{
  "texts": [
    "Impact of Interpretability and Explainability on Trust and AdoptionThe relationship between the interpretability and explainability of LLMs and their trust and adoption by users has been extensively investigated.",
    "Research indicates a strong correlation between the perceived interpretability of a model and the trust users place in its decisions, suggesting that efforts to enhance interpretability can directly contribute to greater acceptance and use of LLMs [34,4,42,36,43,44,35,44,45,46,47,48].",
    "Similarly, the presence of clear and concise explanations was found to not only increase trust but also improve users' ability to identify and correct errors in model outputs [49,50,51,52,53].",
    "The impact of these factors extends beyond individual users to organizations and regulatory bodies, where interpretability and explainability are increasingly seen as prerequisites for the deployment of AI technologies [54,55,56,57,58,59].",
    "Despite the positive effects of interpretability and explainability, studies caution against over-reliance on these factors alone, advocating for a holistic approach that considers other dimensions of AI ethics and governance [60,61,62]."
  ]
}